ozwell.s1: The two notes are very similar. They both describe the case of a 48-year-old female patient with urinary incontinence and lower abdominal discomfort, who was found to have a retroperitoneal mass near the uterus and right ovary. Both notes detail the imaging studies, surgical exploration, and the eventual diagnosis of a subserosal uterine leiomyoma. The clinical note provides a concise summary of the patient's history, examination, imaging findings, diagnosis, and treatment plan, while the detailed case description offers more in-depth information about the surgical findings and histological examination.
